CASE + Views
🧠 1. CASE (Conditional Logic in SQL)
👉 CASE = “IF–ELSE in SQL”
You use it when you want to:
Categorize data
Apply conditions inside a query
Create new columns based on logic

🔹 Basic Syntax
SELECT column,
CASE
  WHEN condition THEN result
  WHEN condition THEN result
  ELSE result
END AS new_column
FROM table;

📘 Example Table: students
name	marks
Rahul	80
Amit	45
Neha	90
Ravi	30

🔹 Example 1: Pass / Fail
SELECT name,
CASE
  WHEN marks >= 50 THEN 'Pass'
  ELSE 'Fail'
END AS result
FROM students;
👉 Output:
name	result
Rahul	Pass
Amit	Fail
Neha	Pass
Ravi	Fail

🔹 Example 2: Grade System
SELECT name,
CASE
  WHEN marks >= 80 THEN 'A'
  WHEN marks >= 60 THEN 'B'
  WHEN marks >= 40 THEN 'C'
  ELSE 'Fail'
END AS grade
FROM students;

🔹 Example 3: Use CASE with Aggregate
👉 Count pass/fail students
SELECT
SUM(CASE WHEN marks >= 50 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS pass_count,
SUM(CASE WHEN marks < 50 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS fail_count
FROM students;

🔹 Example 4: CASE in ORDER BY
SELECT name, marks
FROM students
ORDER BY 
CASE 
  WHEN marks >= 80 THEN 1
  WHEN marks >= 50 THEN 2
  ELSE 3
END;

🧠 Real-Life Use
Salary category (High / Medium / Low)
Order status (Pending / Completed)
Risk level (Low / Medium / High)

⚠️ Common Mistake
❌ Missing END:
CASE WHEN marks > 50 THEN 'Pass'
👉 ❌ Error

💡 Tip
👉 Always give alias:
END AS result
