🧠 2. Views (Virtual Tables)
👉 View = Saved query (virtual table)
It does NOT store data
👉 It stores the query only

🔹 Why use Views?
Simplify complex queries
Security (hide columns)
Reuse queries

🔹 Create View
CREATE VIEW student_view AS
SELECT name, marks FROM students;

🔹 Use View
SELECT * FROM student_view;
👉 Looks like a table but it’s not

🔹 Example: Complex View
CREATE VIEW high_scorers AS
SELECT name, marks
FROM students
WHERE marks > 70;

🔹 Drop View
DROP VIEW student_view;

🧠 Real-Life Use
Show only required data to users
Hide sensitive data (salary, passwords)
Simplify dashboards

🔥 View vs Table
Feature	View	     Table
Stores data	❌ No        ✅ Yes
Speed	             Slower      Faster
Use	             Logic	      Storage

⚠️ Important Notes
Changes in table → reflect in view
Views can be nested
Some views are not updatable

🔥 Combined Example (CASE + View)
CREATE VIEW student_result AS
SELECT name,
CASE
  WHEN marks >= 50 THEN 'Pass'
  ELSE 'Fail'
END AS result
FROM students;
